Call for Papers
( First Announcement )
International Symposium on Manufacturing Strategy ( ISMS '98 ) held in association with Japan Production & Inventory Control Society Annual Meeting ( JPICS- AM '98 )
18 - 20 November , 1998 at International Conference Centre , Waseda University , Tokyo , Japan
Manufacturing strategy is receiving greater attention as a point of focus as companies and industries direct their efforts towards survival in the face of increasing global competition . Rapid changes in market environments and the advent of new kinds of advanced manufacturing systems are calling for novel perspectives which can lead to a better understanding of the intrinsic nature and essential role of manufacturing strategy .
ISMS '98 will provide challenging opportunities to explore new paradigms of manufacturing strategy for the next Millennium . The symposium is designed to create an open forum for bringing together the community of researchers and industrialists who are carrying out innovative studies in manufacturing strategy and related subjects within universities and companies throughout the world .
It is especially appropriate that ISMS '98 will be held in Japan , a country with a strong manufacturing tradition , because only recently has Japanese academia and industry started to recognise manufacturing strategy as an identifiable discipline . The symposium therefore offers a unique opportunity for delegates from Japan and other countries to meet and compare experiences from different cultural and economic contexts .
The symposium programme will comprise keynote presentations by distinguished speakers from the academic and business world . Papers will be presented in parallel sessions arranged according to a number of themes . Panel and workshop sessions organised by leading strategy research groups such as 'International Manufacturing Futures Survey Projects' etc . will also be organised where there will be ample opportunity for constructive discussions between delegates . _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _
Topics :
The followings are some of the areas where contributions will be welcome :
( This list is not limited and original papers in other areas closely related to strategy will be considered . ) * General manufacturing strategy issues * Global operations * State of the art in theory and practice * Strategy and performance * International or domestic survey results * Technology development strategy * Strategies in logistics and supply chains * Environmental strategies * New product development strategies * Quality strategy and management * Service strategies * Strategies in other areas of production _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _
